      "author": "zincplusplus",
      "description": "🎉 Major Release\r\n\r\n  This release represents a significant rewrite and modernization of the habit tracker plugin with improved stability, debugging\r\n  capabilities, and user experience.\r\n\r\n  ✨ New Features\r\n\r\n  - Settings Page: Complete settings interface with auto-refresh functionality\r\n  - Folder Picker: Dropdown selector for default path setting\r\n  - Error Recovery: Auto-recovery component that responds to settings changes\r\n  - Hover Actions: Smart action bar with hover-based interactions and intelligent update system\r\n  - Responsive Layout: Full rewrite of CSS for flexible column layout with horizontal scrolling\r\n  - Mobile Support: Improved mobile experience and multi-theme compatibility\r\n  - Enhanced Debugging: Convert debug setting from number to boolean with better override logic\r\n\r\n  🔧 Improvements\r\n\r\n  - Performance: Better state management and code organization\r\n  - Flexibility: Remove hardcoded plugin name for improved component flexibility\r\n  - Layout: Match line length option to span full page width\r\n  - Navigation: Auto-scroll to most recent date for longer lists\r\n  - Styling: Enhanced hover effects and CSS variables for easier customization\r\n  - Documentation: Complete README rewrite with modern structure and updated features\r\n\r\n  🐛 Bug Fixes\r\n\r\n  - Fix subfolder scanning when processing habit folders\r\n  - Improved error handling and stability\r\n  - Better component lifecycle management\r\n\r\n  🧹 Code Quality\r\n\r\n  - Major refactoring for better maintainability\r\n  - Improved component organization\r\n  - Enhanced debugging capabilities\r\n  - Cleaner codebase structure\r\n\r\n  📝 Documentation\r\n\r\n  - Comprehensive README update\r\n  - Removed emoji usage for cleaner documentation\r\n  - Updated feature descriptions and usage instructions\r\n\r\n  ---\r\n  Full Changelog: https://github.com/your-repo/habit-tracker/compare/v1.x...v2.0.0",
